static class NameIndexBean {
 
 
 
			final String name;
 
            final Descriptors descriptors;
 
 
 
			final @Indexed int index;
 
 
 
			public NameIndexBean(String name, Descriptors descriptors, int index) {
 
				super();
 
				this.name = name;
 
                this.descriptors = descriptors;
 
                this.index = index;
 
			}

I am not using any DBRef on my domain objects. I have only used @Document and @Id

PS :
From your comment, How do you get the formatting of @DBRef inline ? (JIRA Question)

Adding Descriptors to NamedIndexBean creates a cycle within the used objects.

ProgramObject -> Descriptors -> NameLongDescriptor -> NameLongBean -> NameIndexBean -+
 
                      ^                                                              |
 
                      +--------------------------------------------------------------+

In 1.4.x you'd likely (though not necessarily, depending on the used data) run into the same problem when writing data to the DBObject.
The cycle occurs just in another step within the process chain, that was subject to change 1.5.RC1 for some refactoring of index creation.

BTW everything between {{ }} is rendered monospaced.

I've added a guard preventing the index resolver to run into a loop while inspecting domain types. Anyway this will not prevent running into the issue when trying to save structures containing cycles (at least for non null values).

Maybe we should head for a more general approach kicking in when actually collecting type information.
